summary.name: Bird Strikes
summary.dataset_description: A dataset containing information about bird strikes incidents involving aircrafts.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?
goals.rationale: This can help identify airports with high bird strike incidents and inform decisions on bird control measures.

goals.question: What is the most common aircraft make and model involved in bird strikes?
goals.rationale: This can help identify aircraft models that are more prone to bird strikes and inform decisions on aircraft design and maintenance.

goals.question: What is the distribution of damage caused by bird strikes?
goals.rationale: This can help identify the severity of bird strikes and inform decisions on aircraft repair and maintenance.

goals.question: What is the trend of bird strike incidents over time?
goals.rationale: This can help identify if bird strike incidents are increasing or decreasing over time and inform decisions on bird control measures.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by airline operator?
goals.rationale: This can help identify airlines with high bird strike incidents and inform decisions on bird control measures.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.countplot(data=data, x='Airport_Name', order=data['Airport_Name'].value_counts().index)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Flight_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Flight_Date'], errors='ignore')
    aircraft_counts = data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].value_counts().head(20)
    sns.barplot(x=aircraft_counts.index, y=aircraft_counts.values)
    plt.title("What is the most common aircraft make and model involved in bird strikes?")
    plt.xlabel("Aircraft Make and Model")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Bird Strikes")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    damage_counts = data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].value_counts()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Flight_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Flight_Date'], errors='ignore')
    data_count = data.groupby('Flight_Date').size().reset_index(name='count')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Flight_Date', y='count', data=data_count)
    plt.title('What is the trend of bird strike incidents over time?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
